sures that cells produce the correct proteins needed for various functions.\n\nIn summary, protein synthesis involves two main parts: transcription, where DNA is used to make mRNA in the nucleus, and translation, where mRNA is used to build proteins in the cytoplasm. This intricate process ensures that cells have the necessary proteins to function properly.",
